The symbol for the well has disappeared,

536
01:05:18,181 --> 01:05:20,182
and a house has been built here.

537
01:06:15,394 --> 01:06:17,307
The ranch is listed in the will.

538
01:06:18,430 --> 01:06:22,127
It’s part of the inheritance of little Joseph Carmichael.
All of five years old at the time.

539
01:06:22,127 --> 01:06:23,687
He got just about everything.

540
01:06:24,340 --> 01:06:25,835
What about the father, Richard?

541
01:06:26,345 --> 01:06:27,218
Bypassed.

542
01:06:28,001 --> 01:06:31,128
Except as his son's guardian and therefore trustee of the estate.

543
01:06:32,009 --> 01:06:36,090
Old man Spencer's daughter was dead,
and obviously he wasn't too fond of his son-in-law.

544
01:06:37,627 --> 01:06:38,747
Yes, but wait...

545
01:06:38,747 --> 01:06:40,347
Richard doesn't get any money.

546
01:06:41,064 --> 01:06:44,819
But he still controls his son and his son is worth a fortune.

547
01:06:45,263 --> 01:06:46,020
Unless...

548
01:06:47,094 --> 01:06:50,977
Unless for some reason the boy dies before attaining the age of 21.

549
01:06:51,529 --> 01:06:54,017
In that case the entire estate goes to charity.

550
01:06:55,486 --> 01:07:00,836
That would have shut Richard out completely.
And there he was with a son who was weak, sickly, bedridden...

551
01:07:00,837 --> 01:07:01,820
Couldn't even walk.

552
01:07:03,210 --> 01:07:05,667
He must have decided not to take a chance on the boy.

553
01:07:06,670 --> 01:07:08,567
The money was just too tempting.

554
01:07:29,803 --> 01:07:31,114
What are you going to tell her?

555
01:07:31,575 --> 01:07:33,712
About the well under the house and the body.

556
01:07:34,237 --> 01:07:35,722
And the medal with the name on it?

557
01:07:35,722 --> 01:07:37,602
No, and nothing about Carmichael.

558
01:07:38,675 --> 01:07:40,172
She'll think you're crazy.

559
01:07:40,634 --> 01:07:42,180
You'll tell her I’m not.

560
01:07:50,654 --> 01:07:53,831
Good evening, Mrs. Grey. I’m John Russell. This is Miss Norman.

561
01:08:01,760 --> 01:08:03,015
Mr Russell...

562
01:08:03,589 --> 01:08:05,942
I wouldn't have listened to your story for two minutes.

563
01:08:06,266 --> 01:08:07,658
I wouldn't have let you in here...

564
01:08:07,868 --> 01:08:10,066
but for something you said on the phone earlier.

565
01:08:10,983 --> 01:08:12,695
You said that this...

566
01:08:13,243 --> 01:08:16,331
seance affair of yours happened three nights ago, right?

567
01:08:16,331 --> 01:08:17,179
That's right.

568
01:08:18,029 --> 01:08:19,548
Well, three nights ago,

569
01:08:19,892 --> 01:08:21,364
on Monday night,

570
01:08:22,427 --> 01:08:24,132
Linda, my daughter,

571
01:08:25,335 --> 01:08:28,870
woke up screaming just after midnight.

572
01:08:29,787 --> 01:08:31,171
She'd had a nightmare.

573
01:08:31,797 --> 01:08:34,899
When I went in to her, she was hysterical. She was sobbing.

574
01:08:34,973 --> 01:08:36,869
I’d never seen her like that before.

575
01:08:37,723 --> 01:08:40,060
I admit she's had nightmares before, but not ...

576
01:08:43,063 --> 01:08:46,118
She said she'd seen... a boy.

577
01:08:46,946 --> 01:08:49,416
Very small, very thin...

578
01:08:50,267 --> 01:08:52,420
Almost gnome-like.

579
01:08:52,420 --> 01:08:55,627
And he was trying to come up through the floor.

580
01:08:57,656 --> 01:08:59,736
And he kept staring at her.

581
01:09:02,386 --> 01:09:04,289
Here, in the middle.

582
01:09:05,920 --> 01:09:08,768
She hasn't been in the room since, or come near. She sleeps with me.

583
01:09:09,803 --> 01:09:11,435
What we want is...

584
01:09:12,099 --> 01:09:15,211
What you want, Mr Russell, is to tear this room apart.

585
01:09:19,053 --> 01:09:21,669
Well, I have your phone number, Mr Russell. I'll have to think about it.

586
01:11:42,432 --> 01:11:43,334
They're still digging,

587
01:11:44,444 --> 01:11:45,880
but they've found the well.

588
01:11:46,860 --> 01:11:47,579
Okay.

589
01:11:54,357 --> 01:11:55,339
Found anything?

590
01:11:55,339 --> 01:11:59,683
No, nothing yet. This is Tony, Mrs. Grey's son. Miss Norman.

591
01:11:59,720 --> 01:12:00,335
Hi!

592
01:12:08,860 --> 01:12:09,531
Thanks.

593
01:12:31,556 --> 01:12:32,812
Get me the flashlight, will you?

594
01:12:32,728 --> 01:12:33,521
Sure.

595
01:12:34,766 --> 01:12:35,935
I think I’ve found something.

596
01:12:37,859 --> 01:12:38,739
What is it?

597
01:12:52,034 --> 01:12:52,978
It’s a hand.

598
01:12:53,467 --> 01:12:54,098
What?

599
01:12:57,101 --> 01:12:58,109
It’s a hand.

600
01:13:00,173 --> 01:13:01,366
I'll call the police.

601
01:13:09,744 --> 01:13:10,575
Nothing more?

602
01:13:11,984 --> 01:13:13,087
It doesn't look like it.

603
01:13:13,684 --> 01:13:15,420
You think there might be something else coming?

604
01:13:15,787 --> 01:13:16,420
No.

605
01:13:18,104 --> 01:13:21,152
Assistant coroner said those bones have been down there maybe 50 years.

606
01:13:22,023 --> 01:13:23,462
Do you have some idea who that child was?

607
01:13:24,067 --> 01:13:24,960
No, not really.

608
01:13:25,839 --> 01:13:26,823
What's "not really" mean?

609
01:13:28,650 --> 01:13:29,546
No.

610
01:13:31,909 --> 01:13:33,618
I want statements from everybody.

611
01:13:34,248 --> 01:13:36,849
Mrs Grey, do you have some other place you could stay for tonight?

612
01:13:36,849 --> 01:13:38,026
Yes, it's all been arranged.

613
01:13:38,026 --> 01:13:38,667
Good.

614
01:13:50,894 --> 01:13:52,374
I think you should have told them.

615
01:13:53,222 --> 01:13:54,277
It’s got to be there.

616
01:13:54,683 --> 01:13:56,660
Without that medal, there's no evidence. There's nothing.

617
01:13:56,739 --> 01:13:57,930
You have the tape.

618
01:13:58,624 --> 01:14:02,503
Tapes can be altered. They know that. You see the expression on his face?

619
01:14:03,180 --> 01:14:05,340
It was obvious you were holding something back.

620
01:14:07,561 --> 01:14:11,073
Look, it’s very late. Why don't you get some rest and I'll talk to you in the morning.

621
01:14:11,073 --> 01:14:12,962
- Fine. Drive carefully.
- You too.

622
01:17:11,776 --> 01:17:12,648
What's the matter?

623
01:17:19,908 --> 01:17:23,028
St. Paul's Church. September 8th, 1900.

624
01:17:24,231 --> 01:17:26,055
Joseph Patrick Carmichael.

625
01:17:26,878 --> 01:17:27,877
It was there?

626
01:17:28,750 --> 01:17:29,430
It was there.

627
01:17:34,305 --> 01:17:38,424
You have to show it to the police.
It’s the only piece of solid evidence we've got.

628
01:17:39,125 --> 01:17:42,204
They didn't see me dig it up. They couldn't find it.
Why should they believe it was there?

629
01:17:42,861 --> 01:17:44,501
You can't just ignore them.

630
01:17:46,032 --> 01:17:48,864
The police ain't gonna trouble themselves with a 70 years old case.

631
01:17:50,123 --> 01:17:51,875
Still, it's an unsolved murder.

632
01:17:51,791 --> 01:17:52,423
No.

633
01:17:53,226 --> 01:17:55,407
Whatever has to be done, has to be done by me.

634
01:17:56,329 --> 01:17:57,727
I’ve got to get to Carmichael.

635
01:17:58,870 --> 01:17:59,839
He won't see you now.

636
01:17:59,839 --> 01:18:00,846
He'll see me.

637
01:18:07,661 --> 01:18:08,441
Senator!

638
01:18:10,238 --> 01:18:12,430
Hey, hold up!

639
01:18:12,430 --> 01:18:15,037
- Senator!
- Wait a minute! Wait a minute now!

640
01:18:15,945 --> 01:18:16,376
Senator!

641
01:18:16,376 --> 01:18:17,711
I’m John Russell.

642
01:18:18,248 --> 01:18:19,697
I'm living in your house.

643
01:18:20,124 --> 01:18:21,044
Senator, look!

644
01:18:21,836 --> 01:18:22,843
I want to show him that.

645
01:18:23,855 --> 01:18:24,588
Let go!

646
01:18:24,589 --> 01:18:25,551
Senator!

647
01:18:26,402 --> 01:18:27,505
It’s a baptism medal.

648
01:18:29,426 --> 01:18:30,704
It's got your name on it.

649
01:18:30,793 --> 01:18:32,073
- You've got him?
- We've got him.

650
01:18:32,099 --> 01:18:33,388
It was buried with the body...

651
01:18:35,709 --> 01:18:36,683
of a little boy.

652
01:18:37,593 --> 01:18:38,297
Senator!

653
01:18:38,868 --> 01:18:40,269
The police know about it.

654
01:18:49,888 --> 01:18:51,408
Who was that? Some kind of crackpot?

655
01:18:52,592 --> 01:18:53,830
I have no idea...

656
01:18:55,057 --> 01:18:56,384
Never mind. Come on!

657
01:19:01,597 --> 01:19:02,325
Dale...

658
01:19:03,329 --> 01:19:06,401
I want you to radio back to... police headquarters.

659
01:19:07,283 --> 01:19:08,657
Captain DeWitt.

660
01:19:09,686 --> 01:19:11,359
Ask him to call me in Spokane...

661
01:19:12,254 --> 01:19:14,007
- this number.
- Yes, sir.

662
01:20:03,265 --> 01:20:05,304
You goddamn son of a bitch.

663
01:20:06,846 --> 01:20:08,109
What is it you want?

664
01:20:10,353 --> 01:20:12,160
What do you want from me?

665
01:20:13,998 --> 01:20:15,830
I’ve done everything I could do.

666
01:20:19,297 --> 01:20:20,640
There's nothing more to do.

667
01:21:02,721 --> 01:21:03,569
Mr. Russell?

668
01:21:03,570 --> 01:21:04,672
Yes.

669
01:21:05,333 --> 01:21:07,084
My name is DeWitt. Captain DeWitt.

670
01:21:07,085 --> 01:21:07,884
Oh yeah.

671
01:21:08,873 --> 01:21:10,189
I’d like to talk to you if I may.

672
01:21:11,005 --> 01:21:12,357
All right. Come in.

673
01:21:19,491 --> 01:21:20,401
Quite a house.

674
01:21:21,357 --> 01:21:22,117
Yes.

675
01:21:24,944 --> 01:21:27,743
You're a musician, a composer. Is that right, Mr Russell?

676
01:21:28,355 --> 01:21:29,139
Yes.

677
01:21:29,717 --> 01:21:32,494
You teach in a course of the Faculty of Music out of the university?

678
01:21:33,137 --> 01:21:33,892
That's right.

679
01:21:35,612 --> 01:21:38,153
Is this where you held your... seance?

680
01:21:38,824 --> 01:21:40,505
What was it you wanted to talk to me about?

681
01:21:45,343 --> 01:21:50,183
You were out at Boeing airfield this morning, Mr Russell.
They told me you caused quite a scene.

682
01:21:50,228 --> 01:21:52,900
Screaming, yelling, acting like a lunatic.

683
01:21:54,210 --> 01:21:58,416
Sgt. Durban tells me you were up to some strange things last night, too.

684
01:21:59,582 --> 01:22:03,198
Seems you dug up some bones under a lady's house that...

685
01:22:03,265 --> 01:22:06,384
some ghostly voice told you were there. Is that correct?

686
01:22:06,384 --> 01:22:10,040
Only Sgt. Durban said you told him you had no idea...

687
01:22:10,839 --> 01:22:13,167
who those bones were. No idea at all.

688
01:22:13,167 --> 01:22:14,591
Now it seems...

689
01:22:15,570 --> 01:22:17,515
Well, it seems a little odd then, don't you think,

690
01:22:18,311 --> 01:22:23,628
that you go charging across that airfield this morning,
making crazy accusations against Senator Carmichael.

691
01:22:23,630 --> 01:22:24,923
I made no accusation.

692
01:22:23,922 --> 01:22:28,139
- Senator Carmichael who has served this state for 36 years.
- I told you...

693
01:22:28,139 --> 01:22:32,026
And who is not about to give in to any dirty little blackmail scheme.

694
01:22:32,027 --> 01:22:33,427
- Blackmail?
- You heard me.

695
01:22:33,427 --> 01:22:34,292
What are you talking about?

696
01:22:40,462 --> 01:22:43,269
I understand you lost your wife and daughter a little while ago.

697
01:22:44,030 --> 01:22:45,302
Maybe it shook you up.

698
01:22:45,922 --> 01:22:47,002
Maybe too much.

699
01:22:47,409 --> 01:22:48,736
Maybe you need help.

700
01:22:51,010 --> 01:22:52,313
I’d like you to leave now.

701
01:22:52,313 --> 01:22:53,537
We can see that you get it.

702
01:22:55,506 --> 01:22:56,601
You understand what I’m saying?

703
01:22:56,870 --> 01:22:58,016
Out. Now.

704
01:22:58,016 --> 01:22:59,102
Listen to me, Russell.

705
01:23:02,531 --> 01:23:04,291
You've got something of the Senator's.

706
01:23:04,922 --> 01:23:05,952
He wants it back.

707
01:23:06,605 --> 01:23:09,333
It’s a little gold medal. A family heirloom. He lost it.

708
01:23:10,998 --> 01:23:12,574
He thinks you've got it.

709
01:23:14,956 --> 01:23:16,472
I don't know what you're talking about.

710
01:23:22,424 --> 01:23:26,081
I’m sorry to barge in on you like this, but I am so damn mad!

711
01:23:26,082 --> 01:23:27,082
This mor...

712
01:23:28,086 --> 01:23:30,854
This is... Cpt. DeWitt. He's with the police.

713
01:23:30,854 --> 01:23:33,031
You're... Miss Norman?

714
01:23:34,316 --> 01:23:34,952
Yes.

715
01:23:38,274 --> 01:23:42,922
I take it now or I come back in an hour with
a warrant and a crew and we tear this place apart.

716
01:23:43,803 --> 01:23:46,555
Tear this place apart? What's going on here?

717
01:23:46,555 --> 01:23:47,587
I'll be here.

718
01:23:50,479 --> 01:23:51,526
Suit yourself.

719
01:23:56,149 --> 01:23:57,932
Well, what was that all about?

720
01:23:57,933 --> 01:24:00,885
Senator Carmichael thinks he's being blackmailed.

721
01:24:05,472 --> 01:24:07,315
They've cancelled your lease.

722
01:24:07,316 --> 01:24:10,217
They've forced me to resign from the Society.

723
01:24:10,682 --> 01:24:14,481
No explanation, no reason, nothing. Just get out.

724
01:24:14,935 --> 01:24:17,246
I've an appointment with the head of the Board of Directors.

725
01:24:17,593 --> 01:24:19,056
I'll see what I can find out.

726
01:24:20,130 --> 01:24:21,707
I'll call you and let you know.

727
01:25:50,521 --> 01:25:51,183
Yes?

728
01:25:52,729 --> 01:25:53,441
Yes, Claire.

729
01:25:53,441 --> 01:25:56,415
I was driving by and I recognized the car.

730
01:25:56,415 --> 01:25:59,457
I don't know how it happened. I don't know how it could've happened.

731
01:25:59,457 --> 01:26:01,551
There were no other car there. Nothing.

732
01:26:01,551 --> 01:26:03,959
And it's upside down in the middle of the road.

733
01:26:04,169 --> 01:26:09,415
And that man, that policeman who was just at your house, DeWitt, he's dead!

734
01:26:51,355 --> 01:26:53,082
Carmichael. Any messages?

735
01:26:54,792 --> 01:26:57,288
Oh yeah, Cpt. DeWitt. What did he say?

736
01:27:01,316 --> 01:27:01,961
What?

737
01:27:05,088 --> 01:27:05,719
Yeah.

738
01:27:10,436 --> 01:27:11,843
Oh my God!

739
01:27:16,036 --> 01:27:16,483
Who?

740
01:27:18,624 --> 01:27:19,471
Russell?

741
01:27:23,494 --> 01:27:24,229
All right.

742
01:27:27,490 --> 01:27:28,709
Let me have that number.

743
01:27:45,864 --> 01:27:46,759
John Russell.

744
01:27:46,759 --> 01:27:48,241
The Senator is expecting you.

745
01:28:11,047 --> 01:28:12,742
- Still busy?
- Yes.

746
01:28:23,619 --> 01:28:24,409
Where are you going?

747
01:28:24,409 --> 01:28:25,971
I'll be back in a little while.

748
01:28:26,125 --> 01:28:26,789
Claire!

749
01:28:39,042 --> 01:28:41,297
Alright, just what the hell do you want?

750
01:28:42,625 --> 01:28:45,569
You must have some idea, otherwise I wouldn't have got past the door.

751
01:28:46,278 --> 01:28:48,230
I’m a busy man. Make it fast.

752
01:28:53,175 --> 01:28:54,718
The house on Chessman Park.

753
01:28:56,029 --> 01:28:58,439
Your family lived there until 1906.

754
01:29:01,092 --> 01:29:02,667
It’s had a history of...

755
01:29:03,348 --> 01:29:04,805
strange happenings.

756
01:29:05,686 --> 01:29:08,518
There's something... in that house, a manifestation.

757
01:29:10,771 --> 01:29:13,003
This afternoon, Cpt. DeWitt came to see me,

758
01:29:13,396 --> 01:29:14,756
presumably on your behalf.

759
01:29:16,400 --> 01:29:17,975
So, you must have learned what's happened.

760
01:29:17,975 --> 01:29:19,704
At least as much as DeWitt could tell you.

761
01:29:21,234 --> 01:29:24,402
The... disturbances, the seance, the bones...

762
01:29:25,377 --> 01:29:26,761
found in the well.

763
01:29:29,070 --> 01:29:30,844
I tried to talk to you at the airport.

764
01:29:32,810 --> 01:29:34,033
I showed you this.

765
01:29:39,016 --> 01:29:40,471
DeWitt said you'd lost it.

766
01:29:44,286 --> 01:29:45,773
I found it in a grave...

767
01:29:46,899 --> 01:29:48,211
where the child was buried.

768
01:29:52,965 --> 01:29:56,459
There's no... logical explanation for what I’m going to say to you now.

769
01:29:58,314 --> 01:30:00,072
The boy was badly crippled.

770
01:30:01,820 --> 01:30:03,331
I believe he was killed...

771
01:30:04,031 --> 01:30:05,796
in an attic room of that house.

772
01:30:08,726 --> 01:30:09,869
I...

773
01:30:12,155 --> 01:30:13,588
I saw what happened.

774
01:30:16,858 --> 01:30:19,529
And I believe it was Richard Carmichael, your father,

775
01:30:22,169 --> 01:30:24,209
who murdered the boy, his natural son...

776
01:30:24,742 --> 01:30:26,027
Joseph Carmichael.

777
01:30:28,734 --> 01:30:31,814
There was a... substitution from the Sacred Heart orphanage,

778
01:30:32,497 --> 01:30:33,710
the boy was taken to Europe,

779
01:30:34,885 --> 01:30:37,300
cured, miraculously, and returned...

780
01:30:38,304 --> 01:30:39,651
to inherit an empire.

781
01:30:41,682 --> 01:30:43,389
That changeling was you.

782
01:30:57,419 --> 01:30:58,402
So...

783
01:30:59,438 --> 01:31:00,698
That's your story?

784
01:31:01,396 --> 01:31:02,818
Whatever you want to call it.

785
01:31:08,153 --> 01:31:08,833
How much?

786
01:31:09,785 --> 01:31:10,817
My God!

787
01:31:11,521 --> 01:31:14,849
Alright, how much do you want for this farce that you've concocted?

788
01:31:15,407 --> 01:31:17,080
This isn't blackmail.

789
01:31:17,080 --> 01:31:19,520
I’ve been dealing with vermin like you for years.

790
01:31:20,197 --> 01:31:21,541
You waste your chance...

791
01:31:21,541 --> 01:31:26,157
- then you come up with a story that's so pathetically incredible...
- It truly terrifies you, doesn't it?

792
01:31:26,708 --> 01:31:29,339
- It’s the truth. It won't be buried.
- Get out!

793
01:31:29,591 --> 01:31:31,684
None of this belongs to you!

794
01:31:31,643 --> 01:31:34,378
Get out of here! With your filthy lies!

795
01:31:34,378 --> 01:31:37,996
It should've gone to that dead child.
You suspected something was wrong all your life.

796
01:31:37,996 --> 01:31:39,692
